<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="4759088">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>The easiest way:</p>

<ul>
<li>define your classes in "classes" directory</li>
<li>init application like shown below</li>
<li>name class filenames as their lowercase class name with .php suffix (MyClass =&gt; classes/myclass.php)</li>
</ul>

<p>Init code:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">set_include_path</span> ( <span class="hljs-string">"./classes"</span> );
<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">spl_autoload_register</span> ();

<span class="hljs-comment">//class is automatically loaded from ./classes/myclass.php</span>
<span class="hljs-variable">$object_instance</span> = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> <span class="hljs-title class_">MyClass</span> ();
</code></pre>
    </div>
